{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885833406,"sessionID":"ses_284f65075ffed4fZcwkZb7CWPi","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0a4f29001qHcv0k4Twykta8","messageID":"msg_d7b0a41c3001UE5714SNn4DGB8","sessionID":"ses_284f65075ffed4fZcwkZb7CWPi","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_2bce66fe05624624bdccd789","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md","content":"# AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 Tasks\n\n**Module:** integrations  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Plugin Bootstrap and Entry Point\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create main.py entry point\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py`\n  - Import: `Plugin`, `DifyPluginEnv` from `dify_plugin`\n  - Code: `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n  - Verify: File exists with correct entry point\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Create requirements.txt with pinned dependencies\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n  - Add: `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`\n  - Add: `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n  - Verify: Both dependencies listed with correct version bounds\n\n- [ ] **T1.3** Create .difyignore for packaging\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore`\n  - Add common ignore patterns (e.g., `__pycache__`, `*.pyc`, `.git`)\n  - Verify: File exists with ignore patterns\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Plugin Manifest (manifest.yaml)\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Define manifest top-level metadata\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml`\n  - Add: `version: 0.0.2`\n  - Add: `type: plugin`\n  - Add: `author: volcano-sh`\n  - Add: `name: agentcube`\n  - Verify: All fields present\n\n- [ ] **T2.2** Add multilingual labels and descriptions\n  - Add: `label` with keys `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` → `Agentcube`\n  - Add: `description` with multilingual strings for each locale\n  - Verify: All 4 locales present in both label and description\n\n- [ ] **T2.3** Configure icon resources\n  - Add: `icon: icon.png`\n  - Add: `icon_dark: icon-dark.png`\n  - Verify: Both icon fields reference correct files\n\n- [ ] **T2.4** Define resource requirements and permissions\n  - Add: `resource` block with:\n    - `memory` specification\n    - `permission` subtree with flags: `tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage`\n  - Verify: Resource block complete with all permission flags\n\n- [ ] **T2.5** Register tool provider in manifest\n  - Add: `plugins.tools: [provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n  - Verify: Tool provider path listed\n\n- [ ] **T2.6** Add meta section with runtime metadata\n  - Add: `meta.version` matching plugin version\n  - Add: `meta.arch: [amd64, arm64]`\n  - Add: `meta.runner` with `language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`\n  - Add: `meta.minimum_dify_version: null`\n  - Verify: All meta fields present\n\n- [ ] **T2.7** Add optional metadata fields\n  - Add: `created_at` timestamp\n  - Add: `privacy` reference\n  - Add: `repo` URL\n  - Add: `verified` flag\n  - Verify: Optional fields present\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Tool Provider Descriptor (provider/agentcube.yaml)\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Create provider directory structure\n  - Directory: `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/`\n  - Verify: Directory exists\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Define provider identity\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml`\n  - Add: `identity.author: agentcube`\n  - Add: `identity.name: agentcube`\n  - Add: `identity.label` with multilingual strings\n  - Add: `identity.description` with multilingual strings\n  - Add: `identity.icon: icon.png`\n  - Verify: All identity fields present\n\n- [ ] **T3.3** List associated tools\n  - Add: `tools: [tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n  - Verify: Tool path listed\n\n- [ ] **T3.4** Configure Python source entry\n  - Add: `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n  - Verify: Source path points to provider implementation\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: Tool Parameter Schema (tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml)\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Create tools directory structure\n  - Directory: `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/`\n  - Verify: Directory exists\n\n- [ ] **T4.2** Define tool identity\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n  - Add: `identity.name: agentcube-code-interpreter`\n  - Add: `identity.author: agentcube`\n  - Add: `identity.label` with multilingual strings (human + llm)\n  - Add: `identity.description` with multilingual strings (human + llm)\n  - Verify: All identity fields present\n\n- [ ] **T4.3** Define router_url parameter\n  - Add parameter block for `router_url`:\n    - `type: string`\n    - `required: true`\n    - `form: form`\n    - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n  - Verify: Parameter complete\n\n- [ ] **T4.4** Define workload_manager_url parameter\n  - Add parameter block for `workload_manager_url`:\n    - `type: string`\n    - `required: true`\n    - `form: form`\n    - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n  - Verify: Parameter complete\n\n- [ ] **T4.5** Define language parameter (optional select)\n  - Add parameter block for `language`:\n    - `type: select`\n    - `required: false`\n    - `form: llm`\n    - `options: [python, javascript, typescript]`\n    - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n  - Verify: Parameter with options complete\n\n- [ ] **T4.6** Define code parameter (optional)\n  - Add parameter block for `code`:\n    - `type: string`\n    - `required: false`\n    - `form: llm`\n    - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n  - Verify: Parameter complete\n\n- [ ] **T4.7** Define command parameter (optional)\n  - Add parameter block for `command`:\n    - `type: string`\n    - `required: false`\n    - `form: llm`\n    - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n  - Verify: Parameter complete\n\n- [ ] **T4.8** Define session_id parameter (optional)\n  - Add parameter block for `session_id`:\n    - `type: string`\n    - `required: false`\n    - `form: llm`\n    - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n  - Verify: Parameter complete\n\n- [ ] **T4.9** Define session_reuse parameter (optional boolean)\n  - Add parameter block for `session_reuse`:\n    - `type: boolean`\n    - `required: false`\n    - `form: llm`\n    - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n  - Verify: Parameter complete\n\n- [ ] **T4.10** Define code_interpreter_id parameter (optional)\n  - Add parameter block for `code_interpreter_id`:\n    - `type: string`\n    - `required: false`\n    - `form: llm`\n    - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n  - Verify: Parameter complete\n\n- [ ] **T4.11** Configure Python source entry\n  - Add: `extra.python.source: tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n  - Verify: Source path points to tool implementation\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Provider Implementation (provider/agentcube.py)\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Create provider Python module\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n  - Import: `ToolProvider` from `dify_plugin`\n  - Import: `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` from `dify_plugin.errors.tool`\n  - Import: `Any` from `typing`\n  - Verify: Imports present\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Define AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider class\n  - Class: `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider)`\n  - Verify: Class inherits from ToolProvider\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Implement _validate_credentials method\n  - Method: `_validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None`\n  - Wrap validation logic in try-except block\n  - On exception: raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))`\n  - Verify: Method signature and error handling correct\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Tool Implementation (tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py)\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Create tool Python module\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n  - Import: `Generator` from `collections.abc`\n  - Import: `Any` from `typing`\n  - Import: `Tool` from `dify_plugin`\n  - Import: `ToolInvokeMessage` from `dify_plugin.entities.tool`\n  - Import: `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube`\n  - Verify: All imports present\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Define AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool class\n  - Class: `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool)`\n  - Verify: Class inherits from Tool\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Implement _invoke method\n  - Method: `_invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]`\n  - Call: `self.execute(**tool_parameters)`\n  - Yield: `self.create_json_message(result)`\n  - Verify: Method signature and yield pattern correct\n\n- [ ] **T6.4** Implement execute method signature\n  - Method: `execute(self, router_url=None, workload_manager_url=None, language=\"python\", code_interpreter_id=None, session_id=None, code=None, command=None, session_reuse=False, **kwargs)`\n  - Verify: All parameters match tool schema\n\n- [ ] **T6.5** Implement execute method body\n  - Use `CodeInterpreterClient` with `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n  - Handle optional `language` parameter (default `python`)\n  - Handle optional `code` and/or `command` execution\n  - Handle optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, `code_interpreter_id`\n  - Return: JSON-serializable result object\n  - Verify: All parameters handled and result returned\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Documentation Files\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Create README.md\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md`\n  - Include: Plugin overview, installation instructions, usage examples\n  - Verify: File exists with content\n\n- [ ] **T7.2** Create GUIDE.md\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md`\n  - Include: Detailed integration guide for Dify platform\n  - Verify: File exists with content\n\n- [ ] **T7.3** Create PRIVACY.md\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md`\n  - Include: Privacy policy and data handling information\n  - Verify: File exists with content\n\n- [ ] **T7.4** Add icon files\n  - Files: `integrations/dify-plugin/icon.png`, `integrations/dify-plugin/icon-dark.png`\n  - Verify: Both icon files exist\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: Verification and Testing\n\n- [ ] **T8.1** Verify manifest structure\n  - Command: Parse `manifest.yaml` with YAML parser\n  - Check: All required fields present (`version`, `type`, `author`, `name`, `label`, `description`, `icon`, `icon_dark`, `resource`, `plugins.tools`, `meta`)\n  - Verify: Manifest validates successfully\n\n- [ ] **T8.2** Verify provider descriptor structure\n  - Check: `provider/agentcube.yaml` has `identity`, `tools`, `extra.python.source`\n  - Verify: Provider descriptor complete\n\n- [ ] **T8.3** Verify tool schema structure\n  - Check: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` has all 8 parameters defined\n  - Check: Required parameters (`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`) marked as required\n  - Check: Optional parameters marked correctly\n  - Verify: Tool schema complete\n\n- [ ] **T8.4** Verify Python module imports\n  - Command: `python -c \"import provider.agentcube\"` (with dependencies installed)\n  - Command: `python -c \"import tools.agentcube_code_interpreter\"` (with dependencies installed)\n  - Verify: Modules import without errors\n\n- [ ] **T8.5** Verify requirements.txt dependencies\n  - Command: `pip install -r requirements.txt` (dry-run or in venv)\n  - Verify: Dependencies install successfully\n\n- [ ] **T8.6** Verify file structure matches design.md\n  - Check: All 9 files from design.md file map present:\n    - `main.py`, `manifest.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.py`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`, `requirements.txt`, `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore`\n  - Verify: Complete file structure\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `main.py` runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n2. ✅ `manifest.yaml` contains all required top-level keys and structure\n3. ✅ Multilingual labels and descriptions present for 4 locales (en_US, ja_JP, zh_Hans, pt_BR)\n4. ✅ Resource permissions include tool, model, endpoint, app, storage flags\n5. ✅ Tool provider registered in `plugins.tools` list\n6. ✅ Meta section specifies Python 3.12 runner with main entrypoint\n7. ✅ `provider/agentcube.yaml` defines identity, tools list, and Python source\n8. ✅ Tool schema declares all 8 parameters with correct types and forms\n9. ✅ Required parameters (`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`) marked as required=true\n10. ✅ Language parameter offers select options: python, javascript, typescript\n11. ✅ Provider class implements `_validate_credentials` with error handling\n12. ✅ Tool class implements `_invoke` yielding JSON message\n13. ✅ Tool class implements `execute` with all parameters matching schema\n14. ✅ Requirements.txt pins `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n15. ✅ Documentation files present: README.md, GUIDE.md, PRIVACY.md\n16. ✅ Icon files present: icon.png, icon-dark.png\n17. ✅ .difyignore present with common ignore patterns\n18. ✅ File structure matches design.md (11 files total)\n19. ✅ All YAML files parse without syntax errors\n20. ✅ Python modules import successfully with dependencies installed\n\n---\n\n**Notes:**\n- Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (Dify plugin structure created)\n- Uses dify-plugin framework v0.4.x with agentcube-sdk v0.0.10+\n- Python runtime: 3.12 (specified in manifest.meta.runner)\n- Supports amd64 and arm64 architectures\n- Tool provider delegates to AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient\n- Plugin integrates with Dify's tool invocation framework\n- Credential validation raises ToolProviderCredentialValidationError on failure\n- Tool execution returns JSON-serializable results via create_json_message\n- File structure follows Dify plugin conventions from reference implementation\n\n(End of file)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen